2.RERA Bank Account details are taken as per provided by the promoters.

4.We conducted our examination of the Statement in accordance with the Guidance Note on Reports or Certificates for Special Purposes issued
by the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India.
5. The certificate is addressed to and provided to the promoters of the project solely for the purpose to enable comply with requirement of
RERA , and should not be used by any other person or for any other purpose. Accordingly, we do not accept or assume any liability or any duty
of care for any other purpose or to any other person to whom this certificate is shown or into whose hands it may come without our prior
consent in writing

(ADDITIONAL INFORMATION FOR PROJECTS)

If NO
The variation is on account of the following reasons provided by the Promoter of the project.
1.
This certificate is being issued for RERA compliance for the Company Promoter?s Name: PSY Projects Project?s Name: Pramukh Elegance is based
on the records and documents produced before me and explanations provided to me by the management of the Company, based on verification of
books of accounts till 31.10.2019
The physical progress of the project as certified by the architect (Form-1) and engineer (Form- 2) seems in coherence with actual expenditure
incurred & paid considering project specification:

COP Date: 09/08/2012
Place: Ahmedabad
10. The Company has developed 2 difference projects and books of accounts have not been maintained separately . So Total development cost (Excluding
Land Cost) has been apportioned on the basis of Build up area.
6. While computing withdrawals from the bank account, we have considered total receipts during the period and balance lying in RERA Bank
Account as base for computing withdrawable amount on account of construction. Moreover the promotoers have parked 100% the amount
received from the customers in the RERA account as against the requirement of 70%
7 This being very old scheme, KYC and contact details are not readily available with the management. So details is given based on data available at the time of
Certificate
8. Since the scheme has been started before 2011, the carpet area is not available readily so built up area is given instead of Carpet Area.
9 Actual Cost incurred and paid is more that the estimated cost . However due to non editable field, Currently estimated cost is taken as actual cost.
